    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-08-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="49"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Van Valkenburgh</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 45.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States in Japan,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Yedo,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-08-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 23, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the Ono
                    Tomogoro and Matsmoto Judayu, the commissioners recently visiting the United
                    States, and their suite, have returned safely to their country, expressing
                    themselves as well pleased with the manner of their reception and their entire
                    trip.</p>
                <p>So far as I can learn, the government is also pleased with the result of their
                    journey, and I have no doubt it will strengthen their regards for the United
                    States and have a lasting beneficial effect.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, very respectfully, your most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>R. B. VAN VALKENBURGH.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
